OL,3,CMidwife whistleblower calls for change
OL,4,Cdue to 'crisis' in maternity care
OL,6,F"Because on a unit that should be
OL,7,Fstaffed with 16 to 20 midwives, if
OL,8,Fyou've got eight or nine on that day,
OL,9,FI don't have to be a mathematician to
OL,10,Ftell you that is not safe."
OL,12,FIn response, Gill Walton, Chief
OL,13,FExecutive of the Royal College of
OL,14,FMidwives said: "Staffing shortages
OL,15,Fundoubtedly compromise safety,
OL,16,Fsomething that's long been highlighted
OL,17,Fby the Royal College of Midwives, and
OL,18,Fby many reviews into failing maternity
OL,19,Fservices undoubtedly compromise safety.
